The length of the common internal tangent segment <math>XP_3</math> of <math>\Gamma</math> and <math>\omega_3</math> is then <math>\sqrt{8^2-(2+4)^2}=2\sqrt{7}</math>, and it is easily seen that <math>XP_1=4\sin \pi/3=2\sqrt{3}</math>.
