A=(0,8);
B=(12,12);
C=(12,4);
D=(0,0);
E=(0,12);
F=(12,0);
G=(6,4);
H=(6,8);
draw(A--E--B--C--G--H--A--D--F--C);
label("$y$",A--H,S); label("$y$",G--C,N);
</asy>

As you can see from the diagram, the length <math>y</math> fits into the previously blank side, so we know that it is equal to <math>y</math>.

